{"id": "19600", "revid": "24124884", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19600", "title": "The Bloated Float", "text": "The Bloated Float is a boat-turned-&lt;a href=\"Taverns%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt;, docked in the &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20City%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Imperial City&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20City%20Waterfront\"&gt;Waterfront District&lt;/a&gt;. The crew consists of &lt;a href=\"Ormil\"&gt;Ormil&lt;/a&gt; the owner and &lt;a href=\"Graman%20gro-Marad\"&gt;Graman gro-Marad&lt;/a&gt;, the bouncer. It has several tables for eating and a bedroom that the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; can rent for 10 a night.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"An%20Unexpected%20Voyage\"&gt;An Unexpected Voyage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe ship component of the inn is still seaworthy and functional; this is proven in the quest, which is initiated after the Hero rents the room out and sleep for the night. &lt;a href=\"Selene%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Selene&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wrath\"&gt;Wrath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minx\"&gt;Minx&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lynch\"&gt;Lynch&lt;/a&gt;, members of the &lt;a href=\"Blackwater%20Brigands\"&gt;Blackwater Brigands&lt;/a&gt;, take over the ship looking for the Golden Galleon, a supposed treasure."}
{"id": "877961", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=877961", "title": "The Blood-Cursed Town", "text": "The Blood-Cursed Town is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nBackground.\n\"The town of Crestshade has been subjected to a blood-curse that turned the townsfolk feral. While some refugees were able to escape to the south, the mayor remained behind to aid any survivors.\"\nWalkthrough.\nWhen approaching &lt;a href=\"Crestshade\"&gt;Crestshade&lt;/a&gt;, you will run into a woman called &lt;a href=\"Gurhul%20gra-Khazgur\"&gt;Gurhul gra-Khazgur&lt;/a&gt;. She will tell you that the town of Crestshade has been subjected to a blood-curse by &lt;a href=\"Reezal-Jul\"&gt;Reezal-Jul&lt;/a&gt;. Most of the civilians have evacuated, but the mayor is still trapped in the town and refuses to leave. Gurhul will ask you to head into town and rescue the mayor. \nHead up the steps to the village. Along the way, you will spot some ghosts who died in this curse and do not quite understand what is going on. Head past them and into the village itself. The mayor's house will be on the southwest side of town, past a few abandoned houses. Inside, you will find the ghost of &lt;a href=\"Mayor%20Gette\"&gt;Mayor Gette&lt;/a&gt;; talk to her and she will tell you that Reezal-Jul tore her spirit from her body and then used her body and those of others to create some kind of flesh-abomination. She will ask you to help slay the abomination, but first she needs you to help find the spirits of the other victims, as well as find her badge of office. Personal items like the badge can be used to focus energy through, so they can be used to lure the beast out.\nThe objective closest to you will be to find the spirit of &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Tharlas\"&gt;Mage Tharlas&lt;/a&gt;. She will be in the inn across the road from the mayor's house. When you speak to her, she will tell you to go find her staff that she left in the eastern tower. Head due east and across the bridge, and you will find the staff lying at the tower's entrance. While you're here, make sure to pick up the skyshard to the right of the tower. Head back to town and to the west to find &lt;a href=\"Jonne%20Surille\"&gt;Jonne Surille&lt;/a&gt;; his house will be up some flights of stairs. He will tell you to go find his skull, which is somewhere in the graveyard to the south. This is also the general direction where you can find the Mayor's pendant; it will be in the tower south of her residence. The cemetery will be south from the tower, down a slope. If your health is high enough, you can jump off this slope, though jumping from the tower will result in death. There will be several skulls throughout the area; the correct one is lying in front of a building with a statue on top. \nOnce you have all the items, head for the chapel crypts in the west of town and place the items on the altar. This will summon the spirits, and their combined efforts will summon the abomination to this room. Kill it, and the spirit of Mayor Gette will appear. Speak with her and she will thank you for killing the beast, and ask you to give these items a proper burial in the graveyard. Take the items and head for the graveyard; you will find the spirits standing around a hole just left of where you found Jonne's skull. After you bury the items here, the spirits of Tharlas and Jonne will ascend to the afterlife; speak with the Mayor to finish the quest. After this, her spirit will also disappear."}
