{"id": "834007", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=834007", "title": "The Blood-Splattered Shield", "text": "The Blood-Splattered Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nBackground.\n\"Captain Janeve, the shield of the Shornhelm Guard and Countess Tamrith's younger sister, has established a camp for refugees displaced by the campiric menace.\"\nWalkthrough.\nCount Verandis informs the &lt;a href=\"Vestige\"&gt;Vestige&lt;/a&gt; that he knows where Reezal-Jul is. He says Captain Janeve has established a camp for displaced refugees and he wants the Vestige to let Captain Janeve know about Reezal-Jul as he suspects Reezal-Jul had let the refugees survive to serve as a trap.\nThe Vestige journeys to Camp Tamrith. Once there, they warn Captain Janeve that Reezal-Jul is going to attack the camp. Captain Janeve believes she and her group will be ready to defend from \"the mad lizard\" and asks the Vestige to locate Jonah Marose, who had fled the camp with his mother shortly after claiming he could sense Reezal-Jul. The Vestige must travel to &lt;a href=\"Southgard%20Tower\"&gt;Southgard Tower&lt;/a&gt;, where several Montclair Immortals and Knights will attack. Jonah Marose is standing by the tower's entrance, shouting, \"Go away! Leave us alone! I don't want to become a bloodfiend!\" While Jonah runs into the tower for safety, the Vestige will be instructed to defend the tower from &lt;a href=\"House%20Montclair\"&gt;Montclair&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Montclair%20Immortal\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Montclair%20Knight\"&gt;Knights&lt;/a&gt;. \nOnce the threat has been dealt with, the Vestige should climb to the top of Southgard Tower to speak to Jonah Marose. Jonah will mention that Reezal-Jul is approaching with several bloodfiends and refuses to return to the camp believing that the tower is safe enough for him and his mother. The Vestige must return to the camp alone to pass on Jonah's warning. By the time the Vestige returns to Camp Tamrith, an attack has occurred. &lt;a href=\"Florenot%20Eniel\"&gt;Florenot Eniel&lt;/a&gt; will inform the Vestige that &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Online%29\"&gt;vampires&lt;/a&gt; came out of nowhere, half the refugees are dead and Captain Janeve is missing. Healer Odylie is doing what she can to help. The Vestige is instructed to speak to Countess Eselde Tamrith.\nUpon speaking to Countess Tamrith, the Vestige will learn both Captain Janeve and Darien Gautier are absent. Countess Tamrith suggests the Vestige to ask some of the guards for answers as to their whereabouts, as well as pass on some poultice from her. Remic is the only guard who saw Captain Janeve and believes she charged west toward the river, intent on pursuing Reezal-Jul out of contempt toward necromancers. At said location, the Vestige discovers Darien Gautier on the ground and injured among a couple of bodies. Darien is less concerned about himself and more worried about the Captain. He explains that he had followed Captain Janeve during her pursuit of Reezal-Jul and that a group of vampires surrounded them, and while Darien fought the vampires off, Captain Janeve was dragged off into a nearby cave. Darien tells the Vestige to hurry in after her.\nThe Vestige must enter Shadowfate Cavern. Deep inside, the Vestige will discover Jonah Marose who claims that the \"Bad One\" is going to do terrible things to the Captain. Since the cave is full of vampires, Jonah advises the Vestige to use a secret tunnel. Deeper into the cavern, the Vestige must kill several Montclair vampires, including Reezal-Jul. Afterwards, they must search for the Captain who will be standing next to Countess Tamrith. Countess Tamrith explains that the Captain is turning into a vampire and, out of mercy, believes her sister must be killed and avoid turning into a monster.\nThe Vestige is asked to speak to Captain Janeve to offer comfort while the Countess prays over her decision. In contrast to the Countess' suggestion, Captain Janeve wishes to continue living and claims she can control herself, as she knows other vampires have done. It is up to the Vestige to decide what to do about Captain Janeve. If the Vestige chooses to agree with Captain Janeve and spare her, they may leave the cavern and return to where Darien is waiting. The Vestige may also speak to Countess Tamrith, who prays the Vestige's mercy does not turn out to be a terrible mistake."}
