{"id": "1091176", "revid": "5165253", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1091176", "title": "The Blood Pit Wayshrine", "text": "The Blood Pit Wayshrine is a &lt;a href=\"Wayshrines%20%28Online%29\"&gt;wayshrine&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"The%20Deadlands%20%28Online%29\"&gt;The Deadlands&lt;/a&gt; that appears in ."}
{"id": "1093904", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1093904", "title": "The Blood of Nirn", "text": "The Blood of Nirn is a &lt;a href=\"Repeatable%20Quests\"&gt;repeatable&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Online%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in located at &lt;a href=\"Skyreach%20Hold\"&gt;Skyreach Hold&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Craglorn\"&gt;Craglorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\n\"The scholar Nendirume warned me that the Scaled Court has taken over the ruined city of Skyreach. She believes they're searching Skyreach Hold for more of the nirncrux element, which they refer to as \"the blood of Nirn.\"\"\nWalkthrough.\nWhen approaching Skyreach Hold, you will find an Altmer named Nendirume. Talk to her and she will tell you that the &lt;a href=\"Scaled%20Court\"&gt;Scaled Court&lt;/a&gt; have taken over the ancient city in hopes of finding Nirncrux there. She will ask you to help stop them. \nHead across the bridge into Skyreach Hold and proceed through the crridors. In the room with the water, you will have to face off against a boss called &lt;a href=\"Nathrasa%20Shimmerscale\"&gt;Nathrasa Shimmerscale&lt;/a&gt;, who is ver strong and likes to split herself into five Shimmers throughout the fight. Take care when fighting her, or she shimmers could easily overwhelm you. After you kill her, proceed on to the next room and fight the Mantikora there. It is generally a good idea to first focus on the weaker Scaled Court enemies before trying to take down the boss itself. \nProceed on, but take care not to enterthe easternmost chamber, as you will find a powerful boss there that you do not have to face. Instead, head south through the door to the Skyreach Pass. You will be facing several waves of enemies on the bridge here, including no less than three Mantikoras. Take care not to get overwhelmed by the sheer amount of foes, and proceed across the bridge once you have slain them all. Proceed through the ruins on the other side, fighting many more Scaled Court members and Mantikoras along the way. In the room with the water on the side, you will face off against two bosses named &lt;a href=\"Navren%20Daral\"&gt;Navren Daral&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Akkra%20gra-Korma\"&gt;Akkra gra-Korma&lt;/a&gt;; they are quite strong as a pair, so it is a good idea to first focus on killing one and then the other, rather than ocusing on both at the same time. Navren will come charging atyou while Akkra will sling spells from a distance, so it is easier to focus on Navren first. Once both of them lie dead, proceed westward into the caves. \nIn the big room here, you will be fighting a horde of trolls alongside &lt;a href=\"Taskmaster%20Zagrakh\"&gt;Taskmaster Zagrakh&lt;/a&gt;; these are strong, but the real boss will appear after you have killed them. This is a troll called &lt;a href=\"Rakmath%20the%20Breaker\"&gt;Rakmath the Breaker&lt;/a&gt;. Rakmath is powerful, so take care. After defeating him, proceed through the tunnels into the Skyreach Pass. This time, you are passing through the area below the bridge, and you will be facing a boss named &lt;a href=\"Azdarmu%20the%20Awakened\"&gt;Azdarmu the Awakened&lt;/a&gt; alongside a legion of Hoarvors. Azdarmu is not the strongest boss you have faced here; try to attack him from the back and he should not be too difficult. After slaying the beast, head along the stream and down the waterfalls to get back into Skyreach Hold. You will be facing the Scaled Court again, alongside their mantikoras. \nYou will eventually reach a room with piles of Nirncrux strewn about; this is where you will be facing the final boss. His name is Exarch Arnoth, and he has been infused with the power of Nirncrux to make him stronger. At the start of the fight, he will throw fireballs at you; make sure to dodge those. He will also summon balls of fire toward himself; these will heal him if they reach him. After a while, he will forgo the fire and instead try to punch you; try to keep your distance and take him down. Once Arnoth lies dead, proceed ahead through the Outer Halls to the north and leave Skyreach Hold. \nSeek out Nendirume in Dragonstar to finish the quest. She will be in the northwest of town."}
