{"id": "777337", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=777337", "title": "The Bodyguard", "text": "The Bodyguard\u00a0is an optional\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Daggerfall%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0.\u00a0\nDetailed walkthrough.\nAfter going into a random tavern or shop, the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Daggerfall\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; must talk to a &lt;a href=\"Nobles%20%28Daggerfall%29\"&gt;noble&lt;/a&gt; to start the quest. While talking to them, they will ask the Hero to protect them from assassins at a random residence in the town/city between a period of 3 hours.\nWhen the 3 hour time limit begins, the noble will leave the building and go to the specified residence. Upon going to the residence during the specified time, the Hero must go to the noble. When info mode is used on the noble, two &lt;a href=\"Assassin%20%28Daggerfall%29\"&gt;assassins&lt;/a&gt; will appear.\nThe assassins will confront the player on sight, asking them to leave and not become further involved. If the player accepts the assassin's offer, the noble will die. The player will be spared, but fail the quest as a result. If the offer is declined, the assassins will proceed to attack.\nAfter killing the assassins, the player can them speak to the noble and receive their reward."}
{"id": "74083", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=74083", "title": "The Bond of Matrimony", "text": "The Bond of Matrimony is a &lt;a href=\"Rings%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; available in .\nSummary.\nThe Bond of Matrimony is a ring given to the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; and spouse, one each, as part of the &lt;a href=\"Marriage%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;marriage&lt;/a&gt; ceremony. Wearing the ring has no effect on the marriage or spouse. It appears that spouses wear this item by default. The ring may be removed from their inventory if they are &lt;a href=\"Followers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;followers&lt;/a&gt;. Furthermore, it is possible for them to sell you the ring.\nEnchanting.\nThis item may be disenchanted by using an &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Enchanter%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Arcane Enchanter&lt;/a&gt; yielding the &lt;a href=\"Blessing%20of%20Mara\"&gt;Blessing of Mara&lt;/a&gt; upon destruction of the ring. However, there is no item that will accept this enchantment, so it cannot be used."}
{"id": "76437", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=76437", "title": "The Bonds of Matrimony", "text": "The Bonds of Matrimony is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in in which the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; attends their wedding ceremony to their soon-to-be spouse.\nWalkthough.\nTo begin the path to marriage, the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Mara%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Temple of Mara&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Riften%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Riften&lt;/a&gt; needs to be visited. Once inside, the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt; should speak with &lt;a href=\"Maramal\"&gt;Maramal&lt;/a&gt;, who\u00a0will offer to sell them an &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Mara%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Amulet of Mara&lt;/a&gt; for 200. When worn, a unique chat option with certain Characters will be added. If the spouse to be is a companion character they must first be hired before the option is unlocked. The other NPCs unlock their option by completing a quest for them. When an NPC has agreed to marry the Dragonborn, they must go to the Temple of Mara to have it arranged, it will usually take place 24 hours after the wedding has been set up. After the ceremony, spouse will ask where do the Dragonborn wants them to live; his/her house or in the Dragonborn's house.\nBeing married grants the following benefits from the spouse:\nFor a list of potential spouses, visit the &lt;a href=\"Marriage%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;marriage&lt;/a&gt; page for descriptions and marriage requirements."}
