{"id": "1032917", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1032917", "title": "Ibaal", "text": "Athyn Rotheran is an &lt;a href=\"Ashlanders%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Ashlander&lt;/a&gt; first encountered in an Ashlander camp near &lt;a href=\"Molag%20Mar%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Molag Mar&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"An%20Armiger%27s%20Duty\"&gt;An Armiger's Duty&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"An%20Armiger%27s%20Duty\"&gt;An Armiger's Duty&lt;/a&gt;.\nIbaal will confront the Vestige when they sneak into his people's camp. Later, he will help the Vestige identify and slay the &lt;a href=\"Ruddy%20Broodmother\"&gt;Ruddy Broodmother&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\nIn the ashlander camp:\n\"Is this why you sneak through our camp, to desecrate our sacred rites? Do the slaves of the false gods fear us so much they won't even face us themselves? Why are you here, Outlander? Answer truthfully and I may only hobble you.\"\nAfter investigating the pilgrim camps:\n\"You have investigated the camps? Do you still believe we are to blame?\"\nAfter finding &lt;a href=\"Baren%20Maloren\"&gt;Baren Maloren&lt;/a&gt; in the tomb:\n\"In hindsight, the wailing was too pathetic to have been the angry dead. What did your sniveling pilgrim have to say for himself?\"\nAfter spotting the Ruddy Broodmother:\n\"\"Was that the creature the pilgrims fear? This \"Rudy Man\" of legend? It is skulking vermin inflated by the lies of a false god, nothing more.\"\"\nOutside the mine:\n\"The Wise Women cannot say if your quarry is what you think, but they have shared their knowledge of dreugh with me. They offer a mixture to lure the creature out. Spill this in the Ruddy Man's den and it will show itself.\"\nAfter slaying the Ruddy Broodmother:\n\"Your stench is proof enough of your deeds. Was this Ruddy Man a worthy foe?\"\nConversations.\nCaptain Naros: \"What now? An Ashlander! Keep your distance! Understand?\"\nIbaal: \"Peace, Armigers. I must speak with the outlander, that is all.\"\nCaptain Naros: \"If you wish to hear him out, I'll permit it, but don't let your guard down.\""}
