{"id": "1019239", "revid": "31026228", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1019239", "title": "Ice Tribe (Dawnstar)", "text": "The Ice Tribe is a group of humanoids that appear in . They live in areas such as &lt;a href=\"Glacier%20Run\"&gt;Glacier Run&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Council\"&gt;Ice Council&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nOn some unknown year in an unknown era, they launched several attacks on the city of &lt;a href=\"Dawnstar%20%28Dawnstar%29\"&gt;Dawnstar&lt;/a&gt; with the help of a traitor, thieves, &lt;a href=\"Trollkin%20%28Dawnstar%29\"&gt;trollkin&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Gehenoth\"&gt;Gehenoth&lt;/a&gt;. They were successful in their first assault, due to one of &lt;a href=\"Governor%20Vinticae\"&gt;Governor Vinticae&lt;/a&gt;'s champions pulling forces away from one of the city gates, and the traitor operating from the inside. It was this attack that led Governor Vinticae to send away his Four Champions, as he could not determine who it was who had betrayed him. It was also in this attack that Governor Vinticae had his &lt;a href=\"Governor%27s%20Journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; stolen. Later, the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Dawnstar\"&gt;Hero of Dawnstar&lt;/a&gt; would find the traitor and return to Dawnstar for the final showdown, where the Ice Tribes released their greatest weapon upon Dawnstar once more.\nFate of the Ice Tribes.\nIf the player fails to defend Dawnstar, the Ice Tribes and their allies destroy the town, and the player flees, dishonored by his failure.\nIf the player succeeds in defending the town and kills the Gehenoth, he is paid 3000, and the Ice Tribes in Dawnstar collapse.\nVariants.\nLike most enemy types in \"Dawnstar\", the members of the Ice Tribe have a multitude of variants. These include:\nRanking.\nMost of the members of the Ice Tribes of Dawnstar follow a simple ranking method where they are given a rank (either Snow, Ice, Winter, or Elemental), and a class (Scout, Warrior, or Leader). The exceptions to this are the Thriceborn and the Dawn Raiders."}
