{"id": "1058857", "revid": "37601705", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1058857", "title": "Hira", "text": "Hira was the last emperor of &lt;a href=\"Yokuda\"&gt;Yokuda&lt;/a&gt;. He persecuted the &lt;a href=\"Ansei\"&gt;Ansei&lt;/a&gt;, and sent his brigand army of &lt;a href=\"Orcs\"&gt;Orcs&lt;/a&gt; and war castoffs to wipe them out. He sent one hundred of his personal guards to arrest the famous &lt;a href=\"Divad%20Hunding\"&gt;Divad Hunding&lt;/a&gt;. His guards managed to capture him until one of them killed his aging mother, which awoke the spirit of the Way in Divad and led to his escape and subsequent resistance against Hira.\nDivad managed to convince his father &lt;a href=\"Frandar\"&gt;Frandar&lt;/a&gt; to go to war against Hira in the &lt;a href=\"War%20of%20the%20Singers\"&gt;War of the Singers&lt;/a&gt;. The Ansei were greatly outnumbered initially, and led Hira's troops from their original invasion point of High Desert to the foot of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Hattu\"&gt;Mount Hattu&lt;/a&gt;. Frandar planned to fight seven battles here, with the &lt;a href=\"Singers\"&gt;Singers&lt;/a&gt; growing in power with the &lt;a href=\"Shehai\"&gt;Shehai&lt;/a&gt; until triumphed over Hira's forces.\nLittle is known of Hira's life or death, save that he had a consort named Elisa."}
{"id": "33838", "revid": "4984687", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33838", "title": "Hiradirge", "text": "The Hiradirge were a renegade wizard group of &lt;a href=\"Ansei\"&gt;Ansei&lt;/a&gt; during the last civil war in &lt;a href=\"Yokuda\"&gt;Yokuda&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey were said to be masters of stone magic. Some say that they were responsible for the destruction of Yokuda. In &lt;a href=\"1E%20792\"&gt;1E 792&lt;/a&gt; they were defeated in battle, and it is said that, since they failed to conquer the continent, they had their revenge on all of Yokuda. The forbidden swordstroke they may have used is thought to be the ancient \"Pankratosword\" technique, said to have been the &lt;a href=\"shehai\"&gt;shehai&lt;/a&gt; of a first-rank Ansei. &lt;a href=\"Rada%20al-Saran\"&gt;Rada al-Saran&lt;/a&gt; claimed to have been able to perform it, but it is unknown if he belonged to the Hiradirge."}
