{"id": "1090354", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1090354", "title": "Hircine (Oblivion)", "text": "Hircine is a &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Prince\"&gt;Daedric Prince&lt;/a&gt; encountered in . He is known as the huntsman of the princes, and the father of manbeasts. He has &lt;a href=\"Hircine%27s%20Shrine\"&gt;a shrine&lt;/a&gt; halfway between &lt;a href=\"Bravil%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Bravil&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20City\"&gt;Imperial City&lt;/a&gt;. \nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Hircine%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Hircine (Quest)&lt;/a&gt;.\nSlay a &lt;a href=\"Unicorn%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Unicorn&lt;/a&gt; for the Daedra Lord Hircine.\nDialogue.\nAt the start of the quest:\n\"Summoned by prey. The hare crouches before the fox's muzzle. Perhaps I shall task you, mortal. Set you to hunt for my amusement. In Harcane Grove is a quarry worthy of the chase. First named, last tamed, the unicorn runs wild there. Bring me this creature's horn, mortal. If you dare.\"\nUpon returning to the shrine:\n\"Yes, hunter, make your offering. Did you taste its flesh and drink its blood? Never waste the spoils of a kill. You've pleased me, hunter. Take my token, and wear it well. Hereafter, take your prey, and whisper my name.\""}
{"id": "871191", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=871191", "title": "Hircine (Online)", "text": "Hircine is a &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Prince\"&gt;Daedric Prince&lt;/a&gt; and Master of the Hunt.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Heart%20of%20the%20Beast\"&gt;The Heart of the Beast&lt;/a&gt;.\nTalk to Hircine's Statue and defeat his aspect of guile, strength, or speed.\n&lt;a href=\"Hircine%27s%20Gift\"&gt;Hircine's Gift&lt;/a&gt;.\nGain Hircine's blessing to become a &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20%28Online%29\"&gt;werewolf&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Senche\"&gt;The Senche&lt;/a&gt;.\nHircine will congratulate the Vestige after they slay &lt;a href=\"The%20Pale%20Senche\"&gt;The Pale Senche&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"A%20Father%27s%20Promise\"&gt;A Father's Promise&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Firwin\"&gt;Firwin&lt;/a&gt; will pray to Hircine to cure her lycantrophy. After she finds out there is no cure for her, she offers him her father's blood to cure her mother.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Great%20Hunt\"&gt;The Great Hunt&lt;/a&gt;.\nHircine speaks with &lt;a href=\"Balorgh\"&gt;Balorgh&lt;/a&gt; and later &lt;a href=\"Hanu\"&gt;Hanu&lt;/a&gt; in his realm. An enormous version of him can be seen in this distance.\nDialogue.\nAfter placing the heart into the bowl:\n\"You are not mere prey, mortal. Yet you aid the Wyrd who still lick their wounds of defeat. Their fall to Brinarch and his reachmen lost them my favor. To earn it back, you must prove yourself a true hunter.\"\nAfter defeating his aspects (as the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20of%20the%20Hunt\"&gt;Spirit of the Hunt&lt;/a&gt;):\n\"So you've succeeded. Impressive. Few best the aspects.\"\nAfter offering &lt;a href=\"Brinarch\"&gt;Brinarch&lt;/a&gt;'s Briarheart:\n\"Ah, the proven hunter. I see you have the briar heart, torn from the chest of the Reachman. His punishment for failure is to roam the Hunting Grounds as prey. His chest, a gaping hollow, a reminder of his weakness.\"\n\"Do you accept my power?\"\n\"Another comes for my blessing? Drink deep, and let the beast behind your eyes take hold. Ah, but is that fear I smell? The young Bosmer fears what the future holds. Her flesh is weak, but not for long.\"\nConversations.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Heart%20of%20the%20Beast\"&gt;The Heart of the Beast&lt;/a&gt;.\nStatue of Hircine: \"A worthy offering. What is it you seek?\"\nWyress Linnae: \"My Prince, we seek to know why\u2014\"\nStatue of Hircine: \"Silence, prey! I speak not to the weak, but to the one who took the heart.\""}
{"id": "269773", "revid": "39973906", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=269773", "title": "Hircine (Quest)", "text": "Hircine is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in . Hircine's followers have told the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; that, in order to summon the &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Prince\"&gt;Daedric Prince&lt;/a&gt;, they must leave an offering of a &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;wolf pelt&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bear%20Pelt%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;bear pelt&lt;/a&gt; at the statue.\nWalkthrough.\nObtain either a &lt;a href=\"Bear%20Pelt%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Bear Pelt&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Pelt%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Wolf Pelt&lt;/a&gt; and go to &lt;a href=\"Hircine%27s%20Shrine\"&gt;Hircine's Shrine&lt;/a&gt; which is south of the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20University%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Arcane University&lt;/a&gt; and northwest of &lt;a href=\"Fort%20Variela\"&gt;Fort Variela&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Hircine\"&gt;Hircine&lt;/a&gt; will ask the Hero to travel to &lt;a href=\"Harcane%20Grove\"&gt;Harcane Grove&lt;/a&gt; in the southwest, to kill a &lt;a href=\"Unicorn%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;unicorn&lt;/a&gt; and bring back its &lt;a href=\"Unicorn%20Horn%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;horn&lt;/a&gt;. The unicorn is guarded by three Minotaur of the Grove, special &lt;a href=\"Minotaur%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Minotaurs&lt;/a&gt;, and the unicorn itself may also be hostile.\nReturn the horn to Hircine, who rewards the Hero with the &lt;a href=\"Savior%27s%20Hide%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Savior's Hide&lt;/a&gt;, one of the best suits of &lt;a href=\"Light%20Armor%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;light armor&lt;/a&gt; in the game, with a &lt;a href=\"Constant%20Effect\"&gt;constant&lt;/a&gt; 25% Spell Resistance.\nMethods to kill the unicorn.\nMethod one.\n&lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;silver weapons&lt;/a&gt; are needed to kill the unicorn. One strategy is to jump up on something and shoot it with silver arrows, then finish it off with a sword or dagger.\nMethod two.\nAnother method would be to mount the Unicorn (by avoiding the Minotaurs completely and approaching it without a weapon drawn), and leading it to fight difficult monsters. Despite its strength, it's just like any other horse in the game, in that it has a slow overall attack speed and a high knockback rate (low agility). Lead it into a confrontation with a quick, difficult creature (Clannfear, Mountain Lions, sometimes the quick attacks of a Black or Brown Bear will finish it), and finish off the creatures (or grab the unicorn horn and run) once the Unicorn is dead. A variant of this method is to ride the unicorn back to the shrine, whereupon dismounting, the other worshippers will attack it.\nMethod three.\nA third method is to mount the unicorn and travel to a high cliff. Jump off the cliff (which is not too high) while riding the unicorn and it will suffer fall damage; repeat until the unicorn has died.\nMethod four.\nAnother Method is to use a destruction staff (e.g. Staff of Shock) and electrocute the Unicorn and Minotaurs. It is also good to have Shadowmere (rewarded after a Dark Brotherhood quest) as she can attract some of the attention (she attacks enemies which makes her useful and is quite fast).\nMethod five.\nTake the unicorn into &lt;a href=\"Cloud%20Ruler%20Temple\"&gt;Cloud Ruler Temple&lt;/a&gt;, close the gates, and let it watch the two &lt;a href=\"Blades%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Blades&lt;/a&gt; fight. This causes it to attack and the Blades will kill it."}
{"id": "124922", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=124922", "title": "Hircine (Skyrim)", "text": "Hircine is a &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Princes\"&gt;Daedric Prince&lt;/a&gt; encountered in . He is the huntsman of the princes, and the father of manbeasts. &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Werewolves&lt;/a&gt; go to his plane upon death.\nInteractions.\n&lt;a href=\"Ill%20Met%20by%20Moonlight\"&gt;Ill Met by Moonlight&lt;/a&gt;.\nHelp or kill &lt;a href=\"Sinding\"&gt;a werewolf&lt;/a&gt; cursed by the Daedra Lord Hircine.\nDialogue.\nUpon killing the &lt;a href=\"White%20Stag\"&gt;White Stag&lt;/a&gt;:\n\"Well met, hunter.\"\nUpon killing Sinding:\n\"You've done well, hunter.\"\nUpon sparing Sinding and killing the hunters:\n\"Well met again, Hunter.\""}
{"id": "964347", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=964347", "title": "Hircine Resists1", "text": " is an &lt;a href=\"Abilities%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt; in that consists of a variety of &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Effects%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;magic effects&lt;/a&gt; that protect the caster from &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al and physical attacks.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Hircine%27s%20Hunt\"&gt;Hircine's Hunt&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; must choose one of &lt;a href=\"Hircine\"&gt;Hircine&lt;/a&gt;'s aspects to fight: Speed, Strength or Guile. Speed turns him into a wolf (very fast), Strength turns him into a bear (very strong) and Guile makes them fight his true form (fast and strong).\nAcquisition.\nAlthough this ability not intended for use by the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt;, it can be acquired on the PC by using the &lt;a href=\"Console%20Commands%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;console commands&lt;/a&gt;:\ncodice_1\ncodice_2\ncodice_3"}
