{"id": "904786", "revid": "26459635", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=904786", "title": "His Greatest Treasure", "text": "His Greatest Treasure is a &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Thieves%20Guild%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in . &lt;a href=\"Quen\"&gt;Quen&lt;/a&gt; deciphered her father's ledger. She asked for my help with what she uncovered.\nBackground.\n\"Quen deciphered her father's ledger. She asked for my help with what she uncovered.\"\nWalkthrough.\nAfter you have finished both \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Double%20Life\"&gt;A Double Life&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Flawless%20Plan\"&gt;A Flawless Plan&lt;/a&gt;,\" you will find a note from Quen in the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%20Den%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Thieves Den&lt;/a&gt;. She asks you to come to her rooftop hideout, as she has deciphered her father's ledger. \nMeet Quen at her rooftop retreat, above the Mages Guild. She will explain that she managed to decode the ledger with the help of &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Sulima\"&gt;Lady Sulima&lt;/a&gt;, and that she now knows where Saroldo's treasure is hidden. It is located directly north of &lt;a href=\"No%20Shira%20Citadel%20Wayshrine\"&gt;No Shira Citadel Wayshrine&lt;/a&gt;; head there to find a dirt mound. Dig up the treasure and take it; Quen will spot some of the mercenaries from Sulima Mansion digging for something. Confront them; they will be hostile. Once they are dead, Sulima herself will show up, surprised that you are here. She will run away; follow her and talk to her. \nSulima had promised her mercenaries a share of the treasure should they find it; it was the only way she could pay their salary. At this point, you can either tell her that what she did was wrong and that she does not deserve a second chance, or you can let Quen decide whether to forgive this crime. If you tell her this is unforgivable, . If you let Quen decide, she will forgive Sulima. Either way, speak with Quen to finish the quest."}
