{"id": "154367", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=154367", "title": "Hjaal River", "text": "The Hjaal River, also referred to as the River Hjaal, is a body of water found in . It is located in the northwest region of &lt;a href=\"Hjaalmarch\"&gt;Hjaalmarch&lt;/a&gt; Hold. The river flows north, into the marshlands near &lt;a href=\"Morthal%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Morthal&lt;/a&gt; and continues until it merges with the &lt;a href=\"Karth%20River\"&gt;Karth River&lt;/a&gt; and finally terminates in the &lt;a href=\"Sea%20of%20Ghosts\"&gt;Sea of Ghosts&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "54246", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54246", "title": "Hjaalmarch", "text": "Hjaalmarch is one of the nine &lt;a href=\"Holds\"&gt;Holds&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt;. Its capital is &lt;a href=\"Morthal%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Morthal&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the smallest &lt;a href=\"Holds\"&gt;Holds&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Hjaal%20River\"&gt;Hjaal River&lt;/a&gt; runs through a large portion of this Hold. Their coat of arms is of a triskele.\nDescription.\nHjaalmarch is located in northern Skyrim, at the mouth of the &lt;a href=\"Karth%20River\"&gt;Karth River&lt;/a&gt;. The capital, Morthal, lies near the center of the hold. The hold borders &lt;a href=\"Haafingar\"&gt;Haafingar&lt;/a&gt;, separated by the Karth River to the northwest, &lt;a href=\"The%20Reach\"&gt;The Reach&lt;/a&gt; to the west, &lt;a href=\"Whiterun%20Hold\"&gt;Whiterun&lt;/a&gt; to the south and &lt;a href=\"The%20Pale\"&gt;The Pale&lt;/a&gt; to the east. Hjaalmarch's most distinct terrain are its swamps and marshes, but it also has snow-covered forests, mountains, and rocky plains, making it arguably the most geographically diverse of Skyrim's holds.\nSitting on the southern edge of the &lt;a href=\"Drajkmyr%20Marsh\"&gt;Drajkmyr Marsh&lt;/a&gt;, dry ground can be hard to come by in Morthal. The town is often shrouded in a thick fog, and ominous twisted trees grow in the surrounding marsh, which is known to contain vampires. Due to this, Morthal is a foreboding place for travelers, many of whom choose to steer clear of the place altogether.\nMorthal is a town shrouded in mystery. Its people are reclusive and wary of newcomers, and only a single lumber camp supports its weak economy. The Jarl is among the most relaxed in Skyrim when it comes to taxation, but Hjaalmarch is also the poorest of the nine holds. Although the hold is still part of the &lt;a href=\"Empire\"&gt;Empire&lt;/a&gt;, the Jarl is unapologetically vague in her enthusiasm for the Imperial Legate stationed in her dwelling. A number of the people in the town are concerned about the prospect of war, since war brings outsiders, and outsiders are not a welcome sight in Morthal. Most would prefer the conflict be kept outside their home, leaving them free to pursue their own interests."}
{"id": "1102482", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1102482", "title": "Hjaalmarch (Online)", "text": "Hjaalmarch is a &lt;a href=\"subzone\"&gt;subzone&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Western%20Skyrim\"&gt;Western Skyrim&lt;/a&gt; in . It is the eastern of the three subzones of Western Skyrim, reaching from the confluence of the &lt;a href=\"Karth%20River\"&gt;Karth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hjaal%20River\"&gt;Hjaal River&lt;/a&gt;s, extending down to the borders of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Reach%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Reach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Whiterun%20Hold\"&gt;Whiterun Hold&lt;/a&gt; and covering the eastern snowy mountains of the region until the border with the &lt;a href=\"The%20Pale\"&gt;Pale&lt;/a&gt;. It borders &lt;a href=\"Karthald\"&gt;Karthald&lt;/a&gt; to the southwest and &lt;a href=\"Haafingar%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Haafingar&lt;/a&gt; to the northwest.\nLocations.\n &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Coast%20Wayshrine\"&gt;Frozen Coast Wayshrine&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Morthal%20Wayshrine\"&gt;Morthal Wayshrine&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Coast\"&gt;Frozen Coast&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Labyrinthian%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Labyrinthian&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Great%20Lift\"&gt;Eastern Great Lift&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Hjaalmarch%20Great%20Lift\"&gt;Hjaalmarch Great Lift&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Morthal%20%28Online%29\"&gt;Morthal&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"The%20Silver%20Cormorant\"&gt;The Silver Cormorant&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Hunter%27s%20House\"&gt;Hunter's House&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Hordrek%27s%20Hunting%20Grounds\"&gt;Hordrek's Hunting Grounds&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Shademother%27s%20Haven\"&gt;Shademother's Haven&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Black%20Morass%20Ritual%20Site\"&gt;Black Morass Ritual Site&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Hailstone%20Valley%20Ritual%20Site\"&gt;Hailstone Valley Ritual Site&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Old%20Karth%20Ritual%20Site\"&gt;Old Karth Ritual Site&lt;/a&gt;\n &lt;a href=\"Storm-