{"id": "11793", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11793", "title": "Hoag Merkiller", "text": "Hoag Merkiller was a &lt;a href=\"Nord\"&gt;Nord&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"High%20King\"&gt;High King&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"First%20Era\"&gt;First Era&lt;/a&gt;. He is considered to be one of the greatest war chiefs of his time and instrumental in the formation of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Empire%20of%20the%20Nords\"&gt;First Empire of the Nords&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe was also known to be a powerful &lt;a href=\"Tongue\"&gt;Tongue&lt;/a&gt;, as it was shown in his battles against &lt;a href=\"Morrowind\"&gt;Morrowind&lt;/a&gt;'s armies\u00a0during the &lt;a href=\"Skyrim%20Conquests\"&gt;Skyrim Conquests&lt;/a&gt;. During this time he purportedly destroyed seventeen &lt;a href=\"Chimer\"&gt;Chimer&lt;/a&gt;i villages and two &lt;a href=\"Dwemer\"&gt;Dwemer&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0strongholds, which led the &lt;a href=\"Dunmer\"&gt;Dunmer&lt;/a&gt; to vilify him as \"Hoaga, the Mouth of Mud,\" a vicious demon with &lt;a href=\"necromantic\"&gt;necromantic&lt;/a&gt; powers.\nHe attended the coronation of Emperor &lt;a href=\"Gorieus\"&gt;Gorieus&lt;/a&gt; on the 23rd of Sun's Dawn in &lt;a href=\"1E%20461\"&gt;1E 461&lt;/a&gt;, along with his father and High King, &lt;a href=\"Kjoric%20the%20White\"&gt;Kjoric the White&lt;/a&gt;. Kjoric later rebelled against the Emperor, but was killed at the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Sungard\"&gt;Battle of Sungard&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"1E%20477\"&gt;1E 477&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"1E%20478\"&gt;1E 478&lt;/a&gt;. After this, the &lt;a href=\"Moot\"&gt;Moot&lt;/a&gt; named Hoag as the new High King.\nHis reign was short-lived however, as he was killed at the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Glenumbra%20Moors%20%28Event%29\"&gt;Battle of Glenumbria Moors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"1E%20480\"&gt;1E 480&lt;/a&gt; or some time between &lt;a href=\"1E%20461\"&gt;1E 461&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"1E%20477\"&gt;1E 477&lt;/a&gt;. He was succeeded by &lt;a href=\"Wulfharth\"&gt;Wulfharth&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "900075", "revid": "36945899", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=900075", "title": "Hoag Stormcloak", "text": "Hoag Stormcloak, also known as the Great Bear of &lt;a href=\"Eastmarch\"&gt;Eastmarch&lt;/a&gt;, was the father of &lt;a href=\"Ulfric%20Stormcloak\"&gt;Ulfric Stormcloak&lt;/a&gt; and the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Stormcloak%20Clan\"&gt;Stormcloak Clan&lt;/a&gt;. He is known to have had a more tolerant approach to the non-&lt;a href=\"Nord\"&gt;Nord&lt;/a&gt;ic population of &lt;a href=\"Windhelm\"&gt;Windhelm&lt;/a&gt; than his son, who banned the &lt;a href=\"Argonian\"&gt;Argonian&lt;/a&gt; population from living within the city walls. He died in &lt;a href=\"4E%20183\"&gt;4E 183&lt;/a&gt;, while Ulfric was imprisoned due to his involvement in the &lt;a href=\"Markarth%20Incident\"&gt;Markarth Incident&lt;/a&gt;. Due to his incarceration, Ulfric was unable to attend the funeral, and had to smuggle his eulogy for his father out of prison in the form of a letter."}
