{"id": "581739", "revid": "32638003", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=581739", "title": "Enamor (Quest)", "text": "Enamor is a &lt;a href=\"Thieves%20Guild%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Thieves Guild&lt;/a&gt; quest in . It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Bal%20Molagmer\"&gt;Bal Molagmer&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nBackground.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; is requested by Gentleman Jim Stacey to retrieve a stolen Glass Dagger called by the same name &lt;a href=\"Enamor%20%28Weapon%29\"&gt;Enamor&lt;/a&gt;, and return it to &lt;a href=\"Salyn%20Sarethi\"&gt;Salyn Sarethi&lt;/a&gt;.\nWalkthrough.\nAfter completing the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Land%20Deed\"&gt;Land Deed&lt;/a&gt;,\" upon speaking to Gentleman Jim Stacey while wearing the Bal Molagmer gloves, he will tell the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; that a fellow thief has made the mistake of stealing the sword of a valiant knight. He will thus task the Nerevarine with returning the sword Enamor to Salyn Sarethi's chest at the &lt;a href=\"Ghostgate\"&gt;Ghostgate&lt;/a&gt;, along with a letter of apology. \nHead to the Ghostgate. you will find Salyn Sarethi's chest in the lower level of the Tower of Dusk. It will be in the room with all the beds, by the side of the last bed on the left. Leave both the sword and the note in the chest.\nAfter doing this, return to Gentleman Jim Stacey in Vivec City."}
