{"id": "37374", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37374", "title": "Enchanted Armor (Morrowind)", "text": "Enchanted Armor is &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; that has been &lt;a href=\"Enchant%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Effects%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;magic effects&lt;/a&gt;. In general, these items appear as &lt;a href=\"Random%20Loot%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;random loot&lt;/a&gt; throughout &lt;a href=\"Morrowind\"&gt;Morrowind&lt;/a&gt;. Several of these items also have a small number of static occurrences. The vast majority are based on common items and are identical in physical appearance to their un-enchanted counterparts."}
{"id": "127671", "revid": "25356303", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=127671", "title": "Enchanted Armor (Oblivion)", "text": "Enchanted armor is &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; that can bestow attribute or skill boosts or abilities to the wearer. Armor is enchanted through the use of &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Gem%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;soul gems&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Enchanting\"&gt;Altar of Enchanting&lt;/a&gt;. They can be more useful than &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; because they are in effect all the time. However, enchanted armor can only be repaired by the &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero of Kvatch&lt;/a&gt; with level 50 in &lt;a href=\"Armorer%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Armorer&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise, &lt;a href=\"Blacksmiths%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;blacksmiths&lt;/a&gt; must be hired to repair it."}
{"id": "210142", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=210142", "title": "Enchanted Armor (Skyrim)", "text": "Enchanted armor can be found as generic &lt;a href=\"Random%20Loot%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;random loot&lt;/a&gt; throughout &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt;. This page serves as a guide to the different types of &lt;a href=\"Armor%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;enchantments&lt;/a&gt; that can be found.\nFor enchanted clothing, see the &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20Clothing%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;main article&lt;/a&gt;.\nVariables.\nTypically there are 4 variables that the game uses to generate enchanted armor. These are:\nAn example of this would be \"Daedric Armor of the Peerless Knight.\" It should be noted that not every single combinations of Quality/Class/Magnitude and Enchantment weapons are available in the game."}
{"id": "32062", "revid": "28124397", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32062", "title": "Enchanted Arrow", "text": "Enchanted arrows are &lt;a href=\"Arrows%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; that have &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Effects%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;magic effects&lt;/a&gt;, but unlike &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;enchanted weapons&lt;/a&gt;, they cannot be recharged or retrieved after firing, as they disappear. Also unlike normal weapons, they cannot be enchanted with &lt;a href=\"Sigil%20Stone%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;sigil stones&lt;/a&gt; or at an &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Enchanting\"&gt;enchanting altar&lt;/a&gt;.\nTypes.\nEnchanted arrows come in all different types, &lt;a href=\"Glass%20Arrow%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Glass&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Arrow%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Daedric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Arrow%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Dwarven&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Arrow%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Elven&lt;/a&gt;, etc. Also, pay attention to the effects, because some have affects in a large area. Ex: Arrow of Cleansing; 40 fire damage in 10 feet for two seconds.\nUsage.\nEnchanted arrows, like enchanted weapons, can be used on &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;ghosts&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;wraiths&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;liches&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unicorn%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;unicorns&lt;/a&gt;, and other enemies unaffected by normal weapons. They are a useful tool for novice archers, because most of them deal some serious damage."}
{"id": "363232", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=363232", "title": "Enchanted Bezoar", "text": "Enchanted Bezoar is a &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Items%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;quest item&lt;/a&gt; in the \"&lt;a href=\"Mehrunes%27%20Razor%20%28Plug-in%29\"&gt;Mehrunes Razor&lt;/a&gt;\", &lt;a href=\"Official%20Plug-ins%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;plug-in&lt;/a&gt;. It is needed to open the &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; door to the &lt;a href=\"Ayleid\"&gt;Ayleid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ayleid%20Ruins%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;ruin&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Varsa%20Baalim\"&gt;Varsa Baalim&lt;/a&gt;. Two of the them are needed to open the seal."}
{"id": "17416", "revid": "36587426", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17416", "title": "Enchanted Chest", "text": "The Enchanted Chest is a &lt;a href=\"Guild%20Perks\"&gt;guild perk&lt;/a&gt; in . It is received by becoming the &lt;a href=\"Arch-Mage\"&gt;Arch-Mage&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Mages%20Guild%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Mages Guild&lt;/a&gt;. It is located inside the &lt;a href=\"Arch-Mage%27s%20Quarters%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Arch-Mage's Quarters&lt;/a&gt;, and once per week can duplicate almost any &lt;a href=\"Alchemy%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;alchemical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ingredients%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;ingredient&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hero%20of%20Kvatch\"&gt;Hero&lt;/a&gt; may need to speak to &lt;a href=\"Raminus%20Polus\"&gt;Raminus Polus&lt;/a&gt; about &lt;a href=\"Alchemy%20Acquisitions\"&gt;Alchemy Acquisitions&lt;/a&gt; after being made Arch-Mage for a short quest regarding the chest before use.\nHistory.\nThe chest was created by &lt;a href=\"Julienne%20Fanis\"&gt;Julienne Fanis&lt;/a&gt; for the previous Arch-Mage &lt;a href=\"Hannibal%20Traven%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Hannibal Traven&lt;/a&gt;. Traven was quite fond of alchemy, and often tasked Fanis with retrieving ingredients for him. Eventually she could not keep up with his requests, so she created the enchanted chest for him. She warns the Hero that she has no idea what will happen if they try to duplicate non-ingredients and will not be held responsible for lost items.\nUse.\nTo use the chest, place a single ingredient inside and return after 24 hours. The ingredient will be duplicated 10 times, leaving 11 inside the chest. Note that attempting to duplicate non-ingredients (weapons, armor, etc.) will not work (they will not duplicate but the chest will still consume them), nor will attempting to duplicate multiple ingredients at a time (they will be consumed and the chest will be empty).\nDo remember to pick up the duplicate ingredients before a week has passed, otherwise the chest will reset and, presumably for the same reason duplicating two or more ingredients at a time will not work, the duplicated ingredients will be destroyed. It should also be noted that the chest cannot be used to duplicate rare ingredients such as &lt;a href=\"Nirnroot%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Nirnroot&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shepherd%27s%20Pie\"&gt;Shepherd's Pie&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pinarus%27%20Prize%20Minotaur%20Horn\"&gt;Pinarus' Prize Minotaur Horn&lt;/a&gt;."}
