{"id": "1071188", "revid": "50075093", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1071188", "title": "Enchanted Clothing (Morrowind)", "text": "Enchanted Clothing are articles of &lt;a href=\"Clothing%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;clothing&lt;/a&gt; that have been &lt;a href=\"Enchant%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; with certain &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Effects%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;magic effects&lt;/a&gt; in . They can be found as &lt;a href=\"Random%20Loot%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;random loot&lt;/a&gt; across &lt;a href=\"Vvardenfell%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Vvardenfell&lt;/a&gt;, and sometimes can be found as static loot, meaning it will be there on every save."}
{"id": "135005", "revid": "17401442", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=135005", "title": "Enchanted Clothing (Skyrim)", "text": "Enchanted Clothing are &lt;a href=\"Clothing%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;articles of clothing&lt;/a&gt; imbued with &lt;a href=\"magical\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Effects%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;effects&lt;/a&gt; by means of &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt;.\nEnchanted clothing is usually employed by characters specializing in &lt;a href=\"The%20Mage%20Stone%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"The%20Thief%20Stone%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;stealth&lt;/a&gt; due to its light weight and bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Tomes%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; and certain thief-based &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;skills&lt;/a&gt;. Most enchanted clothing can be disenchanted using an &lt;a href=\"arcane%20enchanter\"&gt;arcane enchanter&lt;/a&gt; to learn their enchantments. Virtually weightless, enchanted clothing is classed as in the &lt;a href=\"Character%20Menu%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;character menu&lt;/a&gt; and can be worn to reap the benefits of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Mage%20Armor\"&gt;Mage Armor&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0perk.\nMost &lt;a href=\"Robes%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;robes&lt;/a&gt; are not hooded; however, some, such as the Peerless Robes of Alteration, whose image is of a robe without a hood, are. &lt;a href=\"Headgear\"&gt;Headgear&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"circlets\"&gt;circlets&lt;/a&gt; cannot be worn along with hooded robes.\nHowever, there are exceptions to wearing &lt;a href=\"circlets\"&gt;circlets&lt;/a&gt; with hooded robes, such as the &lt;a href=\"Archmage%27s%20Robes\"&gt;Archmage's Robes&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Mythic%20Dawn%20Robes%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Mythic Dawn Robes&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\nTypically worn by mages, robes can be found on the corpses of hostile mages, such as &lt;a href=\"Conjurer%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;conjurers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;necromancers&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"pyromancer\"&gt;pyromancer&lt;/a&gt;s. The teachers at the &lt;a href=\"College%20of%20Winterhold%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;College of Winterhold&lt;/a&gt; sell magic robes based on the school of Magicka in which they specialize. For example, &lt;a href=\"Faralda%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Faralda&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Trainers%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;teaches&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Destruction%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Destruction&lt;/a&gt;, so her wares reflect that school. The robes sold by the teachers matches the &lt;a href=\"Skills%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;skill level&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Court%20Wizard\"&gt;Court Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s of the &lt;a href=\"Jarl\"&gt;Jarl&lt;/a&gt;s also sell various types of mage accoutrements, including robes. Their wares, too, are contingent upon skill level and &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;. A Novice's Robe and Hood can be found on the corpse of a mage in the torture chambers that the Dragonborn encounters while escaping from &lt;a href=\"Helgen\"&gt;Helgen&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Regenerate%20Magicka%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Regenerate Magicka&lt;/a&gt; robes.\nThe following is a list of enchanted robes that improve magicka regeneration. These cover the upper and lower body.\nSchools of Magic robes.\nThe following is a list of enchanted robes from the five schools of magic. They increase magicka regeneration and reduce spell cost. They cover the upper and lower body.\nUnique enchanted clothing.\nThe following are either unique or one-of-a-kind articles of enchanted clothing.\n&lt;a href=\"Creation%20Club\"&gt;Creation Club&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe following are items of enchanted clothing that are a part of Creation Club content."}
