{"id": "172060", "revid": "28124397", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=172060", "title": "Enchanted Jewelry (Oblivion)", "text": "Enchanted Jewelry is &lt;a href=\"Jewelry%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;jewelry&lt;/a&gt; that has been &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; with one or more &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, normally from the &lt;a href=\"Restoration%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Restoration&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Illusion%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Illusion&lt;/a&gt; school, which produce their &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Effects%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;magic effects&lt;/a&gt; when worn.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;Inventory&lt;/a&gt; menu, an info box shows the jewelry's magical effect. By getting your Enchantments very high, you can absorb or reflect an entire spell or normal weapon &lt;a href=\"Damage%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt;, effectively becoming invincible.\nAmulets.\nNamed.\nNamed enchanted amulets are not leveled, and will not normally appear as random loot until level 20.\nRings.\nNamed.\nNamed enchanted rings are not leveled, and will not normally appear as random loot until level 20.\nTrivia.\nInside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Ancestor%20Moths%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Temple of the Ancestor Moths&lt;/a&gt; you will find the \"Shrine of the Moth\" area, which is a large cave with a Blind Monk Prelate who guards the &lt;a href=\"Savilla%27s%20Stone\"&gt;Savilla's Stone&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%20Guild%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Thieves Guild&lt;/a&gt;'s quest \"&lt;a href=\"Turning%20a%20Blind%20Eye\"&gt;Turning a Blind Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\" Kill and loot the Blind Monk, who always carries either a ring or an amulet. If you don't find what you need, you can reload your saved game, and kill the monk again, also the monk respawns after 72 hours, so you can repeat the process if you want to get more Enchanted Jewelry."}
{"id": "984703", "revid": "26208079", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=984703", "title": "Enchanted Plate", "text": "Enchanted Plate is an &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"card\"&gt;card&lt;/a&gt; in .\nStrategy.\nEnchanted Plate can be used to give a friendly creature more &lt;a href=\"Health%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;Health&lt;/a&gt; so that it may survive an attack, or for more defense on a &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;Guard&lt;/a&gt;. It may also be a way to draw an additional card when required."}
{"id": "1063644", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1063644", "title": "Enchanted Ring", "text": "Enchanted Ring may refer to:"}
{"id": "1063643", "revid": "5050218", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1063643", "title": "Enchanted Ring (Legends)", "text": "Enchanted Ring is an &lt;a href=\"Items%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"card\"&gt;card&lt;/a&gt; in that is a part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Tamriel%20Collection\"&gt;Tamriel Collection&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Card%20Pack\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nEnchanted Ring provides +1 attack and +1 health to a &lt;a href=\"Creatures%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;. This can be used to reinforce friendly creatures against enemy attacks and make their own attacks more effective. Any increase in damage is superfluous other than to attack an opponent directly, however, if that creature has the &lt;a href=\"lethal\"&gt;lethal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"keyword\"&gt;keyword&lt;/a&gt;, as a creature with lethal will instantly kill any other creature it attacks. Similarly, improvements in health will be useless against enemy creatures that have lethal themselves.\nEnchanted Ring will also add any other Enchanted Ring cards in the summoner's discard pile, meaning that if the summoner has used one Enchanted Ring previously, another will provide +2/+2 instead, or +3/+3 if two have been used previously. A maximum of three of the same card can be in a deck at once. As such, the maximum gain from Enchanted Rings is +3/+3.\nFurthermore, Enchanted Ring has the &lt;a href=\"Mobilize\"&gt;Mobilize&lt;/a&gt; keyword, allowing it to be played to an empty lane to also summon a 1/1 &lt;a href=\"Recruit%20%28Legends%29\"&gt;Recruit&lt;/a&gt; with the item equipped."}
{"id": "139293", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=139293", "title": "Enchanted Ring (Skyrim)", "text": "The Enchanted Ring is an &lt;a href=\"Nords%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;ancient Nordic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Artifacts%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;artifact&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Saarthal\"&gt;Saarthal&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Arniel%20Gane\"&gt;Arniel Gane&lt;/a&gt;'s expedition.\nAcquisition.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Quests%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Under%20Saarthal\"&gt;Under Saarthal&lt;/a&gt;\" three of these rings are collected in total by the &lt;a href=\"Last%20Dragonborn\"&gt;Dragonborn&lt;/a&gt;. Optionally, the rings can be returned to Arniel afterwards for a small reward of &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe rings can be &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;disenchanted&lt;/a&gt; at an &lt;a href=\"arcane%20enchanter\"&gt;arcane enchanter&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Fortify%20Health%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Fortify Health&lt;/a&gt; enchantment. Otherwise, they can be kept, sold, or can be worn."}
