{"id": "22225", "revid": "5882993", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22225", "title": "Enchanted Weapons", "text": "Enchanted Weapons may refer to:"}
{"id": "149356", "revid": "5064773", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=149356", "title": "Enchanted Weapons (Morrowind)", "text": ""}
{"id": "17295", "revid": "32911304", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17295", "title": "Enchanted Weapons (Oblivion)", "text": "Enchanted weapons are &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; that have been enchanted with one or more &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, normally from the &lt;a href=\"Destruction%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Destruction&lt;/a&gt; school, which produce magical effects when an enemy is struck.\nGhosts.\nEnchanted weapons, along with spells, &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;silver weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Daedric%20Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Daedric weapons&lt;/a&gt;, are the only things that can damage enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;ghosts&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wraith%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;wraiths&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharges.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;inventory menu&lt;/a&gt;, an info box shows the weapon's magical effect and its remaining/maximum charges. Once the weapon's charge has run out, it must be &lt;a href=\"recharged\"&gt;recharged&lt;/a&gt; to continue using the magical effects. However it can still be used as a normal weapon.\nEnchanted properties.\nNot all weapons are named or received from a quest; some of them have generic suffixes with predictable enchantments. The base stats (weight, value, and damage) for these weapons are the same for their &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;generic weapon&lt;/a&gt; counterpart.\nFor example, let's say a \"Mace of Excess\" is found, which causes &lt;a href=\"Burden%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Burden&lt;/a&gt;. It is an &lt;a href=\"Ebony%20Mace%20%28Oblivion%29\"&gt;Ebony Mace&lt;/a&gt; (Stats: 1500 , 39 , 22 ) that simply has the \"Burden 50 pts for 30 secs on Strike\" enchantment attached. The original base stats are not affected by the enchantment. If an enchantment does additional damage (e.g. adds fire damage), the damage is simply added to the base stats (not including the opponent's resistances)."}
{"id": "124373", "revid": "3152371", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=124373", "title": "Enchanted Weapons (Skyrim)", "text": "Enchanted weapons can be found as generic &lt;a href=\"Random%20Loot%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;random loot&lt;/a&gt; throughout &lt;a href=\"Skyrim\"&gt;Skyrim&lt;/a&gt;. This page serves as a guide to the different types of &lt;a href=\"Weapons%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;enchantments&lt;/a&gt;.\nVariables.\nTypically there are four variables that the game uses to generate enchanted weapons. These are:\nAn example of this would be \"Daedric Greatsword of the Vampire.\" It should be noted that not every single combination of Quality/Class/Magnitude and Enchantment weapons are available in the game."}
