{"id": "195631", "revid": "3179980", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=195631", "title": "Enchanter's Tower (Skyrim)", "text": "The Enchanters Tower is a possible addition for the &lt;a href=\"Homestead%20%28Hearthfire%29%23West%20Wing\"&gt;west wing&lt;/a&gt; of a homestead built-in .\nFeatures.\nThe Enchanters Tower is a towered structure that serves as a dedicated place where &lt;a href=\"Enchanting%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt; can be practiced. It offers a wide variety of enchanting themed storage and furnishings, such as braziers and an ornate &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Enchanter%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Arcane Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;. In addition, an armor mannequin and several weapon plaques are available.\nLike the &lt;a href=\"Library\"&gt;Library&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Alchemy%20Laboratory%20%28Skyrim%29\"&gt;Alchemy Laboratory&lt;/a&gt;, a ladder from the second floor leads to a small rooftop balcony. An optional canopy also can be added to the balcony during construction.\nFurnishings.\nThe following is a list of all furnishings that can be added to the Enchanter's Tower. Furnishings can be built manually at the indoor &lt;a href=\"Carpenter%27s%20Workbench\"&gt;Carpenter's Workbench&lt;/a&gt; or added over a period time if done via a &lt;a href=\"Steward%20%28Hearthfire%29\"&gt;Steward&lt;/a&gt;. The cost of asking a steward to furnish the Enchanter's Tower is 2500 .\nAll furnishings are fixed in position and cannot be removed once they are built. The name of the furnishing option does not always accurately describe what will be added, as in some cases additional containers and accessories may be added, along with the main piece of furniture.\nMisc.\nNote that the grand soul gem must be filled with a grand soul, not empty or filled with a lesser soul.\nFull Totals.\nSpecial Totals.\nThese are the total amount of &lt;a href=\"Septim%20%28Coin%29\"&gt;Septims&lt;/a&gt; and totals are needed in other to get the crafted and bought &lt;a href=\"Housebuilding%20Items\"&gt;Housebuilding Items&lt;/a&gt;."}
