{"id": "122145", "revid": "44356307", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=122145", "title": "Rotheran", "text": "Rotheran is a &lt;a href=\"Dunmer%20Stronghold\"&gt;Dunmer Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; in the region of &lt;a href=\"Sheogorad\"&gt;Sheogorad&lt;/a&gt;. The stronghold is split into\u00a0four subsections: the exterior, Propylon Chamber, a communal hut, and an Arena. The stronghold has been taken over by a group of &lt;a href=\"Dunmer%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Dunmer&lt;/a&gt; bandits, led by &lt;a href=\"Llaren%20Terano\"&gt;Llaren Terano&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe majority of characters are located in the Arena section. There are Dunmer watchers, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Khajiit%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Khajiit&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Argonians%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Argonian&lt;/a&gt; prisoners located in the arena pit; some are in locked pens while some are in the midst of an arena fight when the &lt;a href=\"Nerevarine\"&gt;Nerevarine&lt;/a&gt; arrives.\nExterior.\nA large step sided stronghold with a flat rooftop courtyard containing two discrete buildings, the Propylon Chamber and the Communal Hut. While the third building is the entry section to the Arena, the main interior of the stronghold. Two non-hostile female Dunmer are in this area.\nPropylon Chamber.\nThis large structure sits on the southeastern side of the courtyard. The large chamber houses the propylon pillars for &lt;a href=\"Indoranyon%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Indoranyon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valenvaryon%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Valenvaryon&lt;/a&gt;.\nCommunal Hut.\nThis small round building sits on the western side of the courtyard. It is currently being used the main living quarters for the bandits that live here.\nNotable items.\nThe following items are static in the area:\nArena.\nA small entry building sits in the northeast corner of the courtyard. The entrance leads down a wide short ramp to the upper level of the inner stronghold. The upper level consists of a hallway around the inner room. The hallway has three viewing platforms that open onto the large two-story arena. The slavers are spaced around the hallway watching the slaves in the arena.\nThe lower floor of the arena has four locked (level 45) doors, one on each side. The northeast door opens into the hallway. The southeast door contains a room with four &lt;a href=\"Argonians%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Argonian&lt;/a&gt; slaves. The southwestern door contains a small room with a single &lt;a href=\"blighted%20nix-hound\"&gt;blighted nix-hound&lt;/a&gt;. Behind the northwestern door is a room containing four &lt;a href=\"Khajiit%20%28Morrowind%29\"&gt;Khajiit&lt;/a&gt; slaves and a female Dunmer slave.\nCharacters.\nArena floor:\nSoutheast Argonian slave room:\nNorthwest Khajiit slave room:\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Ice%20Blade%20of%20the%20Monarch%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Ice Blade of the Monarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIce Blade of the Monarch is an &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Cult\"&gt;Imperial Cult&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Cult%20Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; which brings the hero to Rotheran. The quest consists of recovering &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Blade%20of%20the%20Monarch%20%28Weapon%29\"&gt;the sword&lt;/a&gt; and rescuing Adusamsi."}
