{"id": "849622", "revid": "32045548", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=849622", "title": "Rotten Bread and Spoiled Meat", "text": "Rotten Bread and Spoiled Meat is a &lt;a href=\"Books%20%28Online%29\"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt; in .\nContents.\nWell, that did it. My last twenty coins frittered away at market so I could eat bad local food for the next few days. I long for the sweet, sweet flavor of the cuisine brought in by Khajiiti peddlers. The things they do with their food!\nOh, I remember the scent of the delicious cakes, wearing fresh glaze as though it were polished armor. Even the meaty stews had a succulent, honeyed sweetness that caressed the tongue and brought shivers of delight. Just the memory makes me ravenous.\nI suppose I'd better go boil up this pickled goose foot or whatever horrible thing it is the butcher sold me. Alas."}
{"id": "24726", "revid": "5215868", "url": "https://elderscrolls.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24726", "title": "Rotten Den", "text": " \nRotten Den is a large cave with several rooms located west of &lt;a href=\"Xedilian\"&gt;Xedilian&lt;/a&gt;, very close to &lt;a href=\"Inlet%20Camp\"&gt;Inlet Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf entering through Deadfall, run past some statues that shoot destruction magic. M'desi's Skull for the \"&lt;a href=\"Hill%20of%20Suicides\"&gt;Hill of Suicides&lt;/a&gt;\" quest is located in a large stone room in the sanctum, at the top of a tall altar in the center of the room.\nWhen entering the sanctum, there are two floors with holes to drop through. For the quickest route, drop down the eastern-most hole for the second drop. Look around for a hollowed amber limb where you drop. Take the first left, then go up to the tunnel on the right. Follow the root tunnel to the ruined stone sanctum. The skull will be on a chest at the foot of a spell-casting &lt;a href=\"Scalon\"&gt;Scalon&lt;/a&gt; statue. Be wary of pike traps.\nIn the encampment, there will be many &lt;a href=\"zealot\"&gt;zealot&lt;/a&gt;s, but lots of gold, scrolls, potions, and occasional armor and weapons."}
